<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-163-206  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 163 206.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics Weekly  March 15 1989 n1452 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Equipment growth forecast. (semiconductors)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gregg, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The worldwide semiconductor equipment and materials market shouldgrow an average of 11.5 percent during 1989, according to SEMI,the international trade association for the industry.andP;  The figureswere released at the 15th Semicon Europa show.andP;  Europeansemiconductor manufacturers were warned that they need to developa semiconductor infrastructure to become a worldwide player,although no new European wafer fabrication facilities are planned.andO;Europe is upgrading existing plants, however, for both in-houseand merchant markets.andP;  In addition, the demand for improved ionimplanters continues to be strong, and Matra Harris Semiconductorhas chosen Applied Materials Inc's 9000 implanter for theproduction of its 1-micron Complementary Metal OxideSemiconductors process in Nantes.andP;  Analysts expect the market fornew materials to expand since chips now have to be fabricated inEurope.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ForecastingTrade and Professional AssociationsSemiconductor IndustryGrowthWorld MarketConferencesEurope.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>